entries.title: Crypto firms Genesis and Gemini charged by SEC with selling unregistered securities
entries.description: The SEC alleged on Thursday that crypto firm Gemini, founded by the Winklevoss twins, and Barry Silbert's Genesis offered and sold unregistered securities.

entries.title: Exxon predicted global warming with remarkable accuracy years ago, study shows
entries.description: A study from two Harvard academics and one from the University of Potsdam in Germany show that incredible accuracy with which Exxon predicted climate change.

entries.title: Meta sues Voyager Labs, saying it created fake accounts to scrape user data
entries.description: Meta alleged that Voyager Labs was improperly creating fake accounts and scaping user data.

entries.title: Nike CEO touts strength in Gen Z China shopper as Covid disruptions dent regional sales
entries.description: Nike's CEO John Donahoe said the company is "really focused" on Gen Z consumers in China and aims to see inventory levels normalized by the end of the fiscal year.

entries.title: More than 360 new UFO cases have been reported to U.S. intelligence agencies since March 2021
entries.description: The total record of bizarre aerial activity now sits at 510.

entries.title: Time for the Fed to declare victory on inflation? Not yet
entries.description: The question now is how much more evidence policymakers will need to see before they take their foot off the brake.

entries.title: President Biden had classified documents in the garage of his Delaware home
entries.description: President Biden is under scrutiny for possessing classified documents as former President Donald Trump faces a criminal probe for a similar situation.

entries.title: Nelson Peltz lays out his case for Disney proxy fight, slams Fox acquisition
entries.description: Disney will be facing Nelson Peltz's Trian Fund Management in a proxy fight.

entries.title: 2022 was one of the top 10 hottest years on record and the warmest La Nina year on record, according to government scientists
entries.description: 2022 was one of the top 10 hottest years on record and the warmest year on record with a La Nina weather pattern, which generally has a cooling effect.

entries.title: Porsche sees small uptick in global sales despite big drop in Taycan EV
entries.description: Porsche said a 16% drop in global sales of its electric Taycan were "due to supply chain bottlenecks and limited component availability."

entries.title: Investing in Space: Digital orbital danger
entries.description: Cybersecurity company SpiderOak raised $16.4 million in an oversubscribed round in a space data encryption push.

entries.title: Electric luxury-car maker Lucid produced more vehicles in 2022 than expected
entries.description: Lucid told investors to expect it to make between 6,000 and 7,000 of its Air sedans in 2022. It was able to beat that total slightly.

entries.title: Iconic Kobe Bryant jersey up for auction, expected to fetch up to $7 million
entries.description: A jersey that Kobe Bryant wore for 25 games during his MVP season is being sold at auction by Sotheby's.

entries.title: Consumer prices fell 0.1% in December, in line with expectations from economists
entries.description: The consumer price index was expected to decrease 0.1% on a monthly basis and increase 6.5% from a year ago in December, according to Dow Jones.

entries.title: FTX founder Sam Bankman-Fried denies stealing user funds and repeats claims of solvency in new post
entries.description: Bankman-Fried repeated several claims which bankruptcy officials and federal regulators have denied or contradicted.

entries.title: UAE sparks furious backlash by appointing Abu Dhabi oil chief as president of COP28 climate summit
entries.description: The UAE said Thursday that the head of state oil giant ADNOC will lead the COP28 climate talks in Dubai later this year, prompting a furious backlash.

entries.title: Assassin's Creed maker Ubisoft sinks to more than seven-year low after slashing guidance, cancelling games
entries.description: Ubisoft shares slumped as low as 18.80 euros apiece Thursday morning, hitting their lowest level in more than seven years.

entries.title: Biggest risk for UK stocks right now is that we don't enter recession, strategist says
entries.description: The biggest risk to the U.K. stock market is avoiding a widely anticipated recession, according to Roger Lee, head of U.K. equity strategy at Investec.

entries.title: The U.S. economy and stocks face a difficult year — and could even lag Europe
entries.description: After a tough 2022, some strategists argue this year could be Europe's time to shine.

entries.title: Bitcoin jumps above $18,000 to highest level in a month, as FTX lawyers recover $5 billion
entries.description: The world's largest digital currency climbed above $18,000 for the first time since Dec. 14, increasing in value by about 5% in the last 24 hours.

entries.title: Chinese hospital says half of its staff got Covid
entries.description: About half of the nearly 2,000 workers at the Beijing Hospital of Traditional Chinese Medicine got Covid-19, director Liu Qingquan said Wednesday.

entries.title: New year, new job? Experts break down if January really is the right time for a new role
entries.description: If you New Year's resolution is to find a new job, you're not alone. Recruitment experts assess if January is the right time for a career change.

entries.title: IEA says clean energy manufacturing set for substantial growth as world enters 'new industrial age'
entries.description: The world is moving into "a new age of clean technology manufacturing" that could be worth hundreds of billions of dollars per year by 2030, the IEA says.

entries.title: China's reopening set to boost Hong Kong's property market as retail leads the recovery: Colliers
entries.description: In light of China's reopening and easing of Covid rules, Hong Kong's property market will be on a path to recovery in 2023, according to Colliers Hong Kong.
